SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1630
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR COLEMAN.
6823S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 192, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to noncommunicable
disease surveillance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 192, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 192.037, to read as
3 follows:
1 192.037. 1. The department of health and senior
2 services shall designate noncommunicable diseases that are
3 of public health concern and enforce adequate orders,
4 findings, rules, and regulations to prevent the spread of
5 such diseases and to determine the prevalence of such
6 diseases within the state.
7 2. The department of health and senior services shall
8 include in its list of noncommunicable diseases that are
9 required to be reported to the department alpha-gal syndrome
10 and Lyme disease.
11 3. Any required noncommunicable disease case report
12 shall be submitted to the department within seven days of
13 receiving a positive laboratory confirmation. The person or
14 entity responsible for submitting the report shall be:
15 (1) For any case other than a case of alpha-gal
16 syndrome, the health care provider treating the patient; and

SB 1630 2
17 (2) For any case of alpha-gal syndrome, the laboratory
18 that finalizes the positive test result.
19 4. A report of alpha-gal syndrome shall be required
20 for an alpha-gal immunoglobulin E level of greater than or
21 equal to one-tenth of one international unit per milliliter
22 or greater than or equal to one-tenth of one kilounit per
23 liter. A laboratory that finalizes such a test result shall
24 report the test result as a case of alpha-gal syndrome using
25 an electronic laboratory reporting system to be developed by
26 the department.
27 5. The department of health and senior services shall
28 follow up on reported cases of alpha-gal syndrome by
29 applying an appropriate random sampling method for
30 confirmation that the cases meet the most current Centers
31 for Disease Control and Prevention surveillance case
32 definition of alpha-gal syndrome.
33 6. The department of health and senior services shall
34 submit an annual report to the Centers for Disease Control
35 and Prevention summarizing its findings related to the
36 reporting and incidence of the diseases included in the list
37 described in subsection 2 of this section.
38 7. Any rule or portion of a rule, as that term is
39 defined in section 536.010, that is created under the
40 authority delegated in this section shall become effective
41 only if it complies with and is subject to all of the
42 provisions of chapter 536 and, if applicable, section
43 536.028. This section and chapter 536 are nonseverable and
44 if any of the powers vested with the general assembly
45 pursuant to chapter 536 to review, to delay the effective
46 date, or to disapprove and annul a rule are subsequently
47 held unconstitutional, then the grant of rulemaking

SB 1630 3
48 authority and any rule proposed or adopted after August 28,
49 2026, shall be invalid and void.
